"from\": 3694, \"to\": 3708}, {\"ngram\": \"chromosomal or hormonal variations\", \"from\": 3718, \"to\": 3752}, {\"ngram\": \"these adults\", \"from\": 3756, \"to\": 3768}, {\"ngram\": \"their assigned sex-gender categories\", \"from\": 3810, \"to\": 3846}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"\\u200b\\u200bIn many cases, these athletes had no idea they had chromosomal variations until the Olympic gender-verification authorities gave them their results, right before their events, and found them ineligible to compete,\\\"notedSlate's Christina Cauterucci.\", \"from\": 3848, \"to\": 4099, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4078, \"end\": 4087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christina_Aguilera\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.745260444712259e-17, \"text\": \"Christina\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christina_Aguilera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christina_Aguilera\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many cases\", \"from\": 3854, \"to\": 3864}, {\"ngram\": \"these athletes\", \"from\": 3866, \"to\": 3880}, {\"ngram\": \"no idea\", \"from\": 3885, \"to\": 3892}, {\"ngram\": \"chromosomal variations\", \"from\": 3902, \"to\": 3924}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic gender-verification authorities\", \"from\": 3931, \"to\": 3974}, {\"ngram\": \"their results\", \"from\": 3985, \"to\": 3998}, {\"ngram\": \"their events\", \"from\": 4013, \"to\": 4025}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Were such \\\"sex testing\\\" more widespread, Republicans and their anti-trans fellow travelers would perhaps be disturbed to learn that biology is not on their side: People with chromosomal variations outside the XX, XY binary are not extremely rare - around 1 in 100 people, more common than identical twins.\", \"from\": 4101, \"to\": 4406, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4310, \"end\": 4312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.671659609351443e-31, \"text\": \"XX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}, {\"begin\": 4314, \"end\": 4316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phenotype\", \"score\": 0.9918832757409454, \"rank\": 0.008183144587498664, \"text\": \"XY\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phenotype\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phenotype\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"such \\\"sex testing\", \"from\": 4106, \"to\": 4123}, {\"ngram\": \"that biology\", \"from\": 4228, \"to\": 4240}, {\"ngram\": \"their side\", \"from\": 4251, \"to\": 4261}, {\"ngram\": \"People\", \"from\": 4263, \"to\": 4269}, {\"ngram\": \"chromosomal variations\", \"from\": 4275, \"to\": 4297}, {\"ngram\": \"100 people\", \"from\": 4361, \"to\": 4371}, {\"ngram\": \"identical twins\", \"from\": 4390, \"to\": 4405}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As New York Times Magazine writer Ruth Padawernotedin an extensive feature on \\\"sex-testing\\\" in sports, endocrinologists and geneticists have for decades challenged the delineations and exclusions such practices purport to draw: \\\"Relying on science to arbitrate the male-female divide in sports is fruitless, they said, because science could not draw a line that nature itself refused to draw.\\\"\", \"from\": 4408, \"to\": 4801, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4411, \"end\": 4434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3298150303351418e-24, \"text\": \"New York Times Magazine\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\"}, {\"begin\": 4442, \"end\": 4446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Book_of_Ruth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0911675077573278e-14, \"text\": \"Ruth\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Book_of_Ruth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Book_of_Ruth\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sex-testing\", \"from\": 4487, \"to\": 4498}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 4503, \"to\": 4509}, {\"ngram\": \"endocrinologists\", \"from\": 4511, \"to\": 4527}, {\"ngram\": \"geneticists\", \"from\": 4532, \"to\": 4543}, {\"ngram\": \"decades\", \"from\": 4553, \"to\": 4560}, {\"ngram\": \"the delineations\", \"from\": 4572, \"to\": 4588}, {\"ngram\": \"exclusions\", \"from\": 4593, \"to\": 4603}, {\"ngram\": \"such practices\", \"from\": 4604, \"to\": 4618}, {\"ngram\": \"science\", \"from\": 4648, \"to\": 4655}, {\"ngram\": \"the male-female divide\", \"from\": 4669, \"to\": 4691}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 4695, \"to\": 4701}, {\"ngram\": \"science\", \"from\": 4735, \"to\": 4742}, {\"ngram\": \"a line\", \"from\": 4758, \"to\": 4764}, {\"ngram\": \"nature\", \"from\": 4770, \"to\": 4776}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not that this has mattered to numerous regulating bodies and gender conformity zealots.\", \"from\": 4803, \"to\": 4890, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"numerous regulating bodies\", \"from\": 4833, \"to\": 4859}, {\"ngram\": \"gender conformity zealots\", \"from\": 4864, \"to\": 4889}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nor has it mattered that their application of this flawed methodology has a foul legacy of excluding athletes of color.\", \"from\": 4891, \"to\": 5010, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their application\", \"from\": 4916, \"to\": 4933}, {\"ngram\": \"this flawed methodology\", \"from\": 4937, \"to\": 4960}, {\"ngram\": \"a foul legacy\", \"from\": 4965, \"to\": 4978}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 4992, \"to\": 5000}, {\"ngram\": \"color\", \"from\": 5004, \"to\": 5009}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Original reporting.\", \"from\": 5014, \"to\": 5033, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Original reporting\", \"from\": 5014, \"to\": 5032}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fearless journalism.\", \"from\": 5034, \"to\": 5054, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Fearless journalism\", \"from\": 5034, \"to\": 5053}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Delivered to you.Will you take the next step to support our independent journalism by becoming a member of The Intercept?\", \"from\": 5055, \"to\": 5176, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the next step\", \"from\": 5086, \"to\": 5099}, {\"ngram\": \"our independent journalism\", \"from\": 5111, \"to\": 5137}, {\"ngram\": \"a member\", \"from\": 5150, \"to\": 5158}, {\"ngram\": \"The Intercept\", \"from\": 5162, \"to\": 5175}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By signing up, I agree to receive emails from The Intercept and to thePrivacy PolicyandTerms of Use.\", \"from\": 5178, \"to\": 5278, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"emails\", \"from\": 5212, \"to\": 5218}, {\"ngram\": \"The Intercept\", \"from\": 5224, \"to\": 5237}, {\"ngram\": \"thePrivacy PolicyandTerms\", \"from\": 5245, \"to\": 5270}, {\"ngram\": \"Use\", \"from\": 5274, \"to\": 5277}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In what Human Rights Watchcalls\\\"practices that violate fundamental rights to privacy and dignity,\\\" sports governing bodies have overwhelmingly selected successful Black athletes for invasive chromosomal, hormone, and genital testing, in order to potentially exclude them from competing.\", \"from\": 5280, \"to\": 5566, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Human Rights\", \"from\": 5288, \"to\": 5300}, {\"ngram\": \"fundamental rights\", \"from\": 5335, \"to\": 5353}, {\"ngram\": \"privacy\", \"from\": 5357, \"to\": 5364}, {\"ngram\": \"dignity\", \"from\": 5369, \"to\": 5376}, {\"ngram\": \"sports governing bodies\", \"from\": 5379, \"to\": 5402}, {\"ngram\": \"successful Black athletes\", \"from\": 5432, \"to\": 5457}, {\"ngram\": \"invasive chromosomal\", \"from\": 5462, \"to\": 5482}, {\"ngram\": \"hormone\", \"from\": 5484, \"to\": 5491}, {\"ngram\": \"genital testing\", \"from\": 5497, \"to\": 5512}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 5517, \"to\": 5522}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Human Rights Watch reported that the athletes targeted for sex testing are \\\"overwhelmingly women of color from the Global South.\\\"\", \"from\": 5567, \"to\": 5696, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Human Rights Watch\", \"from\": 5567, \"to\": 5585}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 5600, \"to\": 5612}, {\"ngram\": \"sex testing\", \"from\": 5626, \"to\": 5637}, {\"ngram\": \"overwhelmingly women\", \"from\": 5643, \"to\": 5663}, {\"ngram\": \"color\", \"from\": 5667, \"to\": 5672}, {\"ngram\": \"the Global South\", \"from\": 5678, \"to\": 5694}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Strict gender conformity requires expansive authoritarian enforcement far beyond the policing of trans and queer communities and individuals.\", \"from\": 5698, \"to\": 5839, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Strict gender conformity\", \"from\": 5698, \"to\": 5722}, {\"ngram\": \"expansive authoritarian enforcement\", \"from\": 5732, \"to\": 5767}, {\"ngram\": \"the policing\", \"from\": 5779, \"to\": 5791}, {\"ngram\": \"trans\", \"from\": 5795, \"to\": 5800}, {\"ngram\": \"queer communities\", \"from\": 5805, \"to\": 5822}, {\"ngram\": \"individuals\", \"from\": 5827, \"to\": 5838}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The fact that cis women are the victims of this discrimination gives no pause to those committed to trans elimination.\", \"from\": 5841, \"to\": 5959, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The fact\", \"from\": 5841, \"to\": 5849}, {\"ngram\": \"cis women\", \"from\": 5855, \"to\": 5864}, {\"ngram\": \"the victims\", \"from\": 5869, \"to\": 5880}, {\"ngram\": \"this discrimination\", \"from\": 5884, \"to\": 5903}, {\"ngram\": \"no pause\", \"from\": 5910, \"to\": 5918}, {\"ngram\": \"trans elimination\", \"from\": 5941, \"to\": 5958}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the same vein, womenboth cis and transhave been attacked in the street by extremists obsessed with identifying and eradicating anyone they feel should not count as women.\", \"from\": 5960, \"to\": 6133, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the same vein\", \"from\": 5963, \"to\": 5976}, {\"ngram\": \"womenboth cis\", \"from\": 5978, \"to\": 5991}, {\"ngram\": \"the street\", \"from\": 6023, \"to\": 6033}, {\"ngram\": \"extremists\", \"from\": 6037, \"to\": 6047}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 6090, \"to\": 6096}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 6127, \"to\": 6132}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Strict gender conformity requires expansive authoritarian enforcement far beyond the policing of trans and queer communities and individuals.\", \"from\": 6134, \"to\": 6275, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Strict gender conformity\", \"from\": 6134, \"to\": 6158}, {\"ngram\": \"expansive authoritarian enforcement\", \"from\": 6168, \"to\": 6203}, {\"ngram\": \"the policing\", \"from\": 6215, \"to\": 6227}, {\"ngram\": \"trans\", \"from\": 6231, \"to\": 6236}, {\"ngram\": \"queer communities\", \"from\": 6241, \"to\": 6258}, {\"ngram\": \"individuals\", \"from\": 6263, \"to\": 6274}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That it is so often Black and other women of color - the women long excluded from the protections bestowed on white womanhood - who are consistently victims of violent gender policing is not merely a happy accident for the racist far right.\", \"from\": 6276, \"to\": 6516, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Black and other women\", \"from\": 6296, \"to\": 6317}, {\"ngram\": \"color\", \"from\": 6321, \"to\": 6326}, {\"ngram\": \"the women\", \"from\": 6329, \"to\": 6338}, {\"ngram\": \"the protections\", \"from\": 6358, \"to\": 6373}, {\"ngram\": \"white womanhood\", \"from\": 6386, \"to\": 6401}, {\"ngram\": \"victims\", \"from\": 6425, \"to\": 6432}, {\"ngram\": \"violent gender policing\", \"from\": 6436, \"to\": 6459}, {\"ngram\": \"a happy accident\", \"from\": 6474, \"to\": 6490}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sex-gender exclusions cannot be disentangled from the historically colonialist, white supremacist project of strict sex categorization and gender enforcement.\", \"from\": 6517, \"to\": 6675, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sex-gender exclusions\", \"from\": 6517, \"to\": 6538}, {\"ngram\": \"the historically colonialist, white supremacist project\", \"from\": 6567, \"to\": 6622}, {\"ngram\": \"strict sex categorization\", \"from\": 6626, \"to\": 6651}, {\"ngram\": \"gender enforcement\", \"from\": 6656, \"to\": 6674}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It would be foolish to suggest that the far right has ever been interested in either biological sciences or, of course, protecting women and women's sports.\", \"from\": 6677, \"to\": 6833, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the far right\", \"from\": 6713, \"to\": 6726}, {\"ngram\": \"either biological sciences\", \"from\": 6755, \"to\": 6781}, {\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 6789, \"to\": 6795}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 6808, \"to\": 6813}, {\"ngram\": \"women's sports\", \"from\": 6818, \"to\": 6832}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If questions of fair competition were really at stake, the fact that Khelif haslost nineprevious career fights against other women, including losing to Irish gold medalist Kellie Harrington in the delayed 2020 Tokyo Olympics, would surely give lie to claims of her indefeasibly unfair advantage.\", \"from\": 6834, \"to\": 7129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6986, \"end\": 6991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_language\", \"score\": 0.9273576617645407, \"rank\": 0.07764776628930546, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_language\"}, {\"begin\": 7006, \"end\": 7023, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kellie_Harrington\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kellie Harrington\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kellie_Harrington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kellie_Harrington\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"questions\", \"from\": 6837, \"to\": 6846}, {\"ngram\": \"fair competition\", \"from\": 6850, \"to\": 6866}, {\"ngram\": \"stake\", \"from\": 6882, \"to\": 6887}, {\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 6903, \"to\": 6909}, {\"ngram\": \"other women\", \"from\": 6953, \"to\": 6964}, {\"ngram\": \"the delayed 2020 Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 7027, \"to\": 7058}, {\"ngram\": \"lie\", \"from\": 7078, \"to\": 7081}, {\"ngram\": \"claims\", \"from\": 7085, \"to\": 7091}, {\"ngram\": \"her indefeasibly unfair advantage\", \"from\": 7095, \"to\": 7128}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The outcry exposes the illogic and intellectual failures of fascistic gender ideology.\", \"from\": 7130, \"to\": 7216, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The outcry\", \"from\": 7130, \"to\": 7140}, {\"ngram\": \"the illogic\", \"from\": 7149, \"to\": 7160}, {\"ngram\": \"intellectual failures\", \"from\": 7165, \"to\": 7186}, {\"ngram\": \"fascistic gender ideology\", \"from\": 7190, \"to\": 7215}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This does not mean, however, that such reactionary campaigns are best defeated with better arguments based in science and reason, in the form of political debate.\", \"from\": 7217, \"to\": 7379, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"such reactionary campaigns\", \"from\": 7251, \"to\": 7277}, {\"ngram\": \"better arguments\", \"from\": 7301, \"to\": 7317}, {\"ngram\": \"science\", \"from\": 7327, \"to\": 7334}, {\"ngram\": \"reason\", \"from\": 7339, \"to\": 7345}, {\"ngram\": \"the form\", \"from\": 7350, \"to\": 7358}, {\"ngram\": \"political debate\", \"from\": 7362, \"to\": 7378}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The misogynistic, racist policing of bodies deserves only our contempt and fierce opposition.\", \"from\": 7380, \"to\": 7473, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The misogynistic, racist policing\", \"from\": 7380, \"to\": 7413}, {\"ngram\": \"bodies\", \"from\": 7417, \"to\": 7423}, {\"ngram\": \"only our contempt\", \"from\": 743